row.Name: System Objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Root type for other utility types

row.Name: Gameplay Objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Root type for gameplay types

row.Name: Inventory
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Root player inventory

row.Name: object_inventory
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Building window inventory

row.Name: Equipment Objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Objects that a present in 3D and 2D world

row.Name: World objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Objects that a present in 3D world

row.Name: Inventory objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Objects that a present only in 2D world

row.Name: Weapons
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! All weapon types

row.Name: Armors
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! All armor types

row.Name: Tools
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! All tool types that can be held in hands and represented in 3D world

row.Name: Indoor static objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Small static objects (furniture, decorations, small devices)

row.Name: Buildings
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Buildings (modular and not)

row.Name: Outdoor static
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Small static objects (devices also)

row.Name: Padded
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Padded armor of all kinds

row.Name: Leather
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Leather armor of all kinds

row.Name: Chainmail
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Chainmail armor of all kinds

row.Name: Scale
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Scale armor of all kinds

row.Name: Plate
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Plate armor of all kinds

row.Name: Shields
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Shields of all kinds

row.Name: Lamp
row.Description: Made by a talented blacksmith using metal and naphtha. Can be used to create a Lamp Post.

row.Name: Primitive Shovel
row.Description: A primitive shovel is a tool required to perform terraforming actions, that means doing things like flattening, raising, and lowering the ground level, and more.

row.Name: Primitive Hammer
row.Description: Can be used as a tool for Construction and Forging.

row.Name: Mallet
row.Description: Mallets are required for most Construction and Masonry recipes and for paving roads.

row.Name: One-handed Swords
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! One handed swords

row.Name: One-handed Maces
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! One handed maces

row.Name: Hand-and-a-half Swords
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! One or two handed swords

row.Name: Two-handed Swords
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Two handed swords

row.Name: Two-handed Axes
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Two handed axes

row.Name: Furniture
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Usable furniture (chairs and tables also)

row.Name: Decorations
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Unusable furniture and decorations

row.Name: Fences
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Mostly decorational fences and small walls

row.Name: Fortifications
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Fortificational buildings and wall modules

row.Name: Storage
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Buildings-containers without much additional logic

row.Name: Mass processing
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Massive refinement buildings

row.Name: Residential
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Buildings with bindspots for living (not customizable)

row.Name: Custom House
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Group of customizable house walls

row.Name: Monuments
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Town/country central objects

row.Name: Combat related
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Combat realted static objects

row.Name: Anvil
row.Description: Created with the Smelting skill. Can be used to construct a Forge and Anvil or Blacksmith's Shop.

row.Name: Windmill
row.Description: Just a simple Mill. For mass production of wheat flour.

row.Name: Water
row.Description: A raw material used for crafting: Furnace, Kiln, Clay Anvil Form, Leather, Bone Glue, Flax Fibers, Unfired Clay Tile, and more.

row.Name: Alchemical Glassware
row.Description: A part of the Alchemist's Table. Created from Glass.

row.Name: Distiller
row.Description: A part of the Alchemist's Table. Created from Copper Ingots.

row.Name: Building Log
row.Description: Used for the construction of massive buildings, such as houses, warehouses, stables, etc.

row.Name: Bark
row.Description: A raw material used to create a Bark Box

row.Name: Branch
row.Description: Branches are one of the basic materials used to make primitive tools, to start a Campfire, and for cooking simple food.

row.Name: Rock
row.Description: A raw material that is primarily used for Masonry and for paving roads. Can be refined into Shaped Rock using a pickaxe.

row.Name: Marble
row.Description: A light-colored stone which may be obtained from the mountains with a pickaxe. Used in some building recipes such as: Fountain, Castle Keep, and for paving roads. Can be refined to Marble Plate using a pickaxe.

row.Name: Granite
row.Description: Can be refined to Shaped Granite, which is a material in most architectural structures. Also can be used for paving roads.

row.Name: Clay
row.Description: A raw material for building. Can be obtained by digging in clay pits with a shovel or pickaxe.

row.Name: Sand
row.Description: Can be used to create building materials: Mortar and Glass.

row.Name: Snow
row.Description: You can melt snow in a Cauldron and get water or make snowballs and snowman. Movement over snow is slowed.

row.Name: Flint Stone
row.Description: Used to create the most primitive tools: Axe, Hammer, Shovel, Pickaxe, Sickle, Knife, and Saw.

row.Name: Silkworm Cocoon
row.Description: Can be harvested from mulberry trees. Used to create Silk Filaments.

row.Name: Handle
row.Description: A wooden processed material used to create tools.

row.Name: Wheel
row.Description: Mainly used to make Transportation Carts with the Carpentry skill.

row.Name: Charcoal
row.Description: Fuel for a fire wherever it is needed, from a Campfire to a Blacksmith's Shop or Kitchen. Crafted from Billets using a Kiln.

row.Name: Hank of Linen
row.Description: Required to craft Linen Cloth. Crafted from Flax Fiber using a Spinning Wheel.

row.Name: Linen Cloth
row.Description: Basic cloth that can be used in a variety of Tailoring recipes. Crafted from Hanks of Linen using a Loom.

row.Name: Linen Rope
row.Description: Can be used to make bows and training weapons, build wells, and construct carts. Crafted from Hanks of Linen with a Weaver's Toolkit.

row.Name: Hank of Silk
row.Description: Required to craft Silk Cloth. Crafted from Silk Filaments with a Spinning Wheel.

row.Name: Silk Cloth
row.Description: A cloth that's used to craft decorated clothes and high level armor. Crafted from Hanks of Silk using a Loom.

row.Name: Hank of Wool
row.Description: Required to craft Wool Cloth. Crafted from Wool Packs with a Spinning Wheel.

row.Name: Wool Cloth
row.Description: A cloth that's used to craft decorated clothes and high level armor. Crafted from Hanks of Wool with a Loom.

row.Name: Clay Tile
row.Description: A material that's used in buildings. Crafted from Unfired Clay Tile in Kiln

row.Name: Shaped rock
row.Description: Building material that's primarily used for Masonry recipes. Crafted from Rock using a pickaxe.

row.Name: Marble Plate
row.Description: Building material for such recipes as a Fountain or Castle Keep. Crafted from Marble using a pickaxe.

row.Name: Shaped Granite
row.Description: Building material for most architectural constructions. Crafted from Granite using a pickaxe.

row.Name: Glass
row.Description: Can be made in a Kiln by melting Sand. Required for such recipes as a Window Module, Bottle, and Alchemical Glassware.

row.Name: Unfired Vase
row.Description: A blank for creating a Vase. Crafted from Clay at a Potter's Wheel.

row.Name: Unfired Masterwork Vase
row.Description: A blank for creating a Masterpiece Vase. Crafted from Clay at a Potter's Wheel.

row.Name: Unfired Urn
row.Description: A blank for creating an Urn. Crafted from Clay at a Potter's Wheel.

row.Name: Clay Anvil Form
row.Description: Put this form and 8 Iron Ingots into a Furnace to create an Anvil.

row.Name: Nails
row.Description: Used for building and manufacturing shields and furniture. Crafted from lumps of metal in a Forge on an Anvil.

row.Name: Metal Band
row.Description: Used for building and manufacturing shields and furniture. Crafted from metal bars in a Forge on an Anvil.

row.Name: Metal Sheet
row.Description: Used for building and manufacturing shields and furniture. Crafted from metal ingots in a Forge on an Anvil.

row.Name: Lock
row.Description: A metal part that's used to craft Door Modules and Gate Modules. Crafted from metal bars in a Forge on an Anvil.

row.Name: Empty Bottle
row.Description: Used with the Brewery skill for bottling alcoholic beverages. Crafted from Glass with a Glassblower's Toolkit.

row.Name: Door Module
row.Description: A part of a big number of building recipes. Crafted on a Workbench by carpenters.

row.Name: Gate Module
row.Description: A major part of various gatehouses. Crafted on a Workbench by carpenters.

row.Name: Window Module
row.Description: A part of a large number of building recipes. Crafted on a Workbench by carpenters.

row.Name: Carpenter's Toolkit
row.Description: A toolkit used to create furniture parts and wooden equipment with the Carpentry skill.

row.Name: Glassblower's Toolkit
row.Description: A toolkit used to create glassware with the Material Preparation skill.

row.Name: Weaver's Toolkit
row.Description: A toolkit used to create ropes, bags, and clothing.

row.Name: Hardwood Billet
row.Description: Sawed off of hardwood logs: Birch, Elm, Maple, and Oak. Can be used as fuel as is or can be refined into Charcoal.

row.Name: Softwood Billet
row.Description: Sawed off of softwood logs: Apple, Spruce, Pine, Mulberry, and Aspen. Can be used as fuel as is or can be refined into Charcoal.

row.Name: Hardwood Board
row.Description: Sawed off of hardwood logs: Birch, Elm, Maple, Oak. Used for building, carpentry, and to craft shields and bows.

row.Name: Softwood Board
row.Description: Saw off of softwood logs: Apple, Spruce, Pine, Mulberry, and Aspen. Used for building, carpentry, and to craft shields and bows.

row.Name: Iron Ore
row.Description: A natural material that can be obtained with a pickaxe from mining iron blocks in tunnels. Can be smelted into Iron Ingots, Iron Bars, and Lumps of Iron.

row.Name: Copper Ore
row.Description: A natural material that can be obtained with a pickaxe from mining copper blocks in tunnels. Can be smelted into Copper Ingots, Copper Bars, and Lumps of Copper.

row.Name: Gold Ore
row.Description: A natural material that can be obtained with a pickaxe from mining gold blocks in tunnels. Can be smelted into Gold Ingots, Gold Bars, and Lumps of Gold.

row.Name: Silver Ore
row.Description: A natural material that can be obtained with a pickaxe from mining silver blocks in tunnels. Can be smelted into Silver Ingots, Silver Bars, and Lumps of Silver.

row.Name: Fertile Soil
row.Description: Ideal soil for growing crops. Produces better yields than regular soil. Also used to make an Herbal Garden.

row.Name: Intestines
row.Description: Can be used as an ingredient in several different cooking recipes: Cake with Giblets, Apple Berry Pie, Pork Sausage, and Venison Bratwurst Sausage.

row.Name: Egg
row.Description: Can be used as an ingredient in several different cooking recipes: Boiled Eggs, Pasta, Fried Eggs, Goulash, Eggnog, Cabbage Pies, Fried Salmon Patties, Egg Pies, Omelets, Beef Stew, Fish Cakes, King's Beef Stew, Yorkshire Pudding, and Beef Cabbage Hash.

row.Name: Milk
row.Description: Can be used as an ingredient in several different cooking recipes: Apple Hamburg Soup, Cheese, Milky Bread, Milky Salmon, Cookies, Egg Pies, Eggnog, Julienne, Mutton with Peas, Norman Bread, Omelets, Venison Bratwurst Sausage, Yorkshire Pudding, Venison Stew, and Waterzooi.

row.Name: Bones
row.Description: Animal part salvaged from any slain animal. It is used in the creation of Bone Glue and some decorative constructions.

row.Name: Horn
row.Description: Animal part salvaged from Moose, Deer, Aurochs Bulls or Aurochs Cows. It is used in the creation of Composite Bows.

row.Name: Feathers
row.Description: Collected from chickens when they are slaughtered in or outside the coop. Used in the creation of arrows.

row.Name: Wool Pack
row.Description: Obtained from mature sheep in a barn. Can be refined into Hanks of Wool with a Spinning Wheel.

row.Name: Naphtha
row.Description: A flammable liquid created by Alchemists. It is used in the creation of lamps, explosives, and fire arrows.

row.Name: Big Deer Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Deer. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Big Moose Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Moose. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Big Bear Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Bear. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Wheat
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used to make Flour and Malt. Can be used as animal feed.

row.Name: Peas
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used for various cooking recipes. Can be used as animal feed.

row.Name: Cabbage
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used for various cooking recipes. Can be used as animal feed.

row.Name: Onion
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used for various cooking recipes.

row.Name: Carrot
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used for various cooking recipes. Can be used as animal feed.

row.Name: Grapes
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Primarily used for making Wine.

row.Name: Mushroom
row.Description: An ingredient for cooking recipes, but it cannot be eaten by itself: Potato with Mushrooms, Codfish with Mushrooms, Julienne, Beast Steak, Vegetable Soup, Chicken Pie, Venison Stew, Meat Kabobs, and Pizza.

row.Name: Flax stem
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Can be refined into Flax Fibers with the Procuration skill.

row.Name: Straw
row.Description: A crop that harvested with wheat. Can be used for construction or as animal feed.

row.Name: Bone Glue
row.Description: Building material, crafted from Bones with the Procuration skill.

row.Name: Flour
row.Description: Crafted from Wheat with Quern-Stone or Windmill. Used in various baking recipes.

row.Name: Honey
row.Description: Honey is collected from beehives. It is an ingredient for some cooking recipes: Berries in Honey, Baklava, Pecene Veprove Koleno, Eggnog, Cookies, Confiture, Mulled Wine, Greatberry Pie, Brewed Honey, and Improper Honey.

row.Name: Flax Fibers
row.Description: Obtained with the Procuration skill from Flax Stems. Can be refined into Hanks of Linen with a Spinning Wheel.

row.Name: Silk Filaments
row.Description: Natural material obtained from mulberry. Can be refined into Hanks of Silk with a Spinning Wheel

row.Name: Beef
row.Description: A type of meat harvested from a bull or cow. It is an ingredient in: Meat Stew, Beef Steak, Beef Stew, King's Beef Stew, Yorkshire Pudding, Apple Meat Loaf, Beef Cabbage Hash, Ravioli, and Cottage Pie.

row.Name: Pork
row.Description: A type of meat harvested from domesticated pigs and an ingredient in: Bacon, Pecene Veprove Koleno, Goulash, Pea Porky Soup, Pork Sausage, Ravioli, Pizza, and Venison Bratwurst Sausage.

row.Name: Mutton
row.Description: A type of meat harvested from domesticated sheep and rams in a barn. It is an ingredient in: Samsa, Mutton Steak, Mutton with Peas, Lamb Stew with Cabbage, Ravioli, Meat Kabobs, Cottage Pie, and Mutton with Peas.

row.Name: Game Meat
row.Description: Meat from wild animals. Used in various cooking recipes.

row.Name: White Meat
row.Description: A meat of slaughtered chicken or rabbit. It is an ingredient in: Boiled Chicken, Crispy Chicken, Stuffed Rabbit, Chicken Pie, Meat Kabobs, and Crispy Chicken.

row.Name: Salmon
row.Description: Can be cooked on a campfire or as an ingredient in Milky Salmon, Fried Salmon Patties, Fish Cakes, Fish Stew, and Fried Salmon.

row.Name: Trout
row.Description: Can be cooked on a campfire or as an ingredient in Apple Hamburg Soup, Fried Trout, Trout in Berry Sauce, and Waterzooi.

row.Name: Herring
row.Description: Can be cooked on a campfire or as an ingredient in Rollmops, Herring Salad, Fish Stew.

row.Name: Codfish
row.Description: Can be cooked on a campfire or as an ingredient in Codfish with Cabbage, Codfish with Mushrooms, Fish Cakes, Cod Chowder, and Fish Stew.

row.Name: Steel Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 2 Iron Ingot and 12 Flux. Used to forge weapons, armor parts and other high-quality metal components.

row.Name: Iron Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 20 Iron Ore. Used to forge weapons, armor parts and other medium-quality metal components.

row.Name: Copper Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 20 Copper Ore. Used in some recipes: Distiller, Kitchen, and Fountain.

row.Name: Vostaskus Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 40 Lumps of Vostaskus Steel. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other metal components of the best quality. Also can be used to create a Hardened Steel Pickaxe, Glorious Monument, and Siege Totem.

row.Name: Silver Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 40 Silver Ore. Used to construct a Fine Monument.

row.Name: Gold Ingot
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 320 Gold Ore. Used to construct a Glorious Monument and is an ingredient of the Battle Totem.

row.Name: Steel Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 2 Iron Bars and 6 Flux. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other high-quality metal components. Ingredient of Irregular Alloy.

row.Name: Iron Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 4 Iron Ore. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other medium-quality metal components.

row.Name: Copper Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 4 Copper Ore. Used in some recipes: Distiller and Cooking Pot.

row.Name: Vostaskus Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 30 Irregular Alloy. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other metal components of the best quality.

row.Name: Silver Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 8 Silver Ore. Can be smelted into lumps and ingots, which are used in jewelry.

row.Name: Gold Bar
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 70 Gold Ore. Can be smelted into lumps and ingots, which are used in jewelry.

row.Name: Lump of Steel
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 2 Lumps of Iron and 2 Flux. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other high-quality metal components.

row.Name: Lump of Iron
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 1 Iron Ore. Used to forge weapons, armor parts, and other medium-quality metal components.

row.Name: Lump of Copper
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 1 Copper Ore. Can be smelted into bars and ingots.

row.Name: Lump of Vostaskus Steel
row.Description: A small piece of Vostaskus. Can be smelted into Vostaskus Bars and Vostaskus Ingots.

row.Name: Lump of Silver
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 1 Silver Ore. Used in the manufacture of jewelry.

row.Name: Lump of Gold
row.Description: Made with the Smelting skill from 8 Gold Ore. Used in the manufacture of jewelry.

row.Name: Thick Leather
row.Description: A material used in the manufacture of leather clothes, outfits, weapons, and armor.

row.Name: Thin Leather
row.Description: A material used in the manufacture of leather clothes, outfits, weapon, and armor.

row.Name: Bear Hide
row.Description: Can be acquired by killing wild Bears and then skinning them. Bear hide can then be hung on a Drying Frame to produce Thick Dried Hide.

row.Name: Fur
row.Description: A type of thin hide that can be obtained by skinning a hare. It can be dried with a Drying Frame to produce Thin Dried Hide.

row.Name: Unfired Clay Tile
row.Description: Created from Clay. Can be refined into Clay Tile with a Kiln.

row.Name: Plant Fiber
row.Description: A plant fiber from mother earth. Used to make Simple Rope and Simple Cloth.

row.Name: Thick Dried Hide
row.Description: Used to make Thick Leather with a Tanning Tub.

row.Name: Thin Dried Hide
row.Description: Used to make Thin Leather with a Tanning Tub.

row.Name: Flux
row.Description: A catalyst created by alchemists. It is used in the production of mortar and steel.

row.Name: Amethyst
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Silver Amethyst Rings and Silver Jeweled Necklaces.

row.Name: Garnet
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Silver Garnet Rings and Silver Jeweled Necklaces.

row.Name: Ruby
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Silver Ruby Rings, Gold Jeweled Necklaces, Exceptional Gold and Silver Rings.

row.Name: Emerald
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Gold Emerald Rings, Gold Jeweled Necklaces, Exclusive Gold and Silver Amulets.

row.Name: Sapphire
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Gold Sapphire Rings, Exceptional Gold and Silver Rings, Exclusive Gold and Silver Amulets.

row.Name: Diamond
row.Description: A precious stone that is used in making Gold Diamond Rings, Exceptional Gold and Silver Rings, Exclusive Gold and Silver Amulets.

row.Name: Jeweler's Toolkit
row.Description: Used to craft rings and amulets with the Jewelry skill.

row.Name: Mortar
row.Description: A building material required in complex structures. Created in a Kiln with 10 Sand, 2 Rocks, and 1 Flux.

row.Name: Edible Berries
row.Description: Can be gathered from Forest Soil. Used in several cooking recipes.

row.Name: Wine
row.Description: An alcoholic beverage made from fermented grapes.

row.Name: Apple
row.Description: Can be gathered from Apple Trees. Used in various cooking recipes and as animal feed.

row.Name: Potato
row.Description: A crop that can be grown by Farmers. Used for various cooking recipes.

row.Name: Dung
row.Description: Collected by cleaning out coops, barns, or stables. Can be used as a fertilizer.

row.Name: Irregular Alloy
row.Description: Used in the production of Vostaskus Ingots. Very few people know the exact recipe.

row.Name: Malt
row.Description: A Wheat product. Used to make Beer with a Brewing Tank.

row.Name: Brewed Honey
row.Description: A product of Honey. Used to make Mead with a Brewing Tank.

row.Name: Fermented Grape
row.Description: A product of Grapes. Used to make Wine with a Brewing Tank.

row.Name: Fermented Apple Juice
row.Description: An Apple product. Used to make Cider with a Brewing Tank.

row.Name: Little Boards
row.Description: Made from regular boards. Used in recipes where a regular Board is too much.

row.Name: Metal Components
row.Description: A metal product used in manufacture of crossbows, warfare gear, and carts.

row.Name: Small Warfare Kit
row.Description: Used to create warfare gear, such as Arrow Stands and Sapper Charges. Crafted in Siege Engineer's Workshop.

row.Name: Medium Warfare Kit
row.Description: Used to create warfare gear, such as Trebuchets and Defensive Fences. Crafted in Siege Engineer's Workshop.

row.Name: Large Warfare Kit
row.Description: Used to create warfare gear, such as Trebuchets and Tents. Crafted in a Siege Engineer's Workshop.

row.Name: Explosive
row.Description: Used to make Sapper Charges. Crafted from Linen Cloth and Naphtha in a Siege Engineer's Workshop.

row.Name: Simple Rope
row.Description: Simple rope made from a bundle of Plant Fiber. Used to make Simple Bows, Light Crossbows, Training Dummies, Practice Weapons, Siege Torches, Small Warfare Kits, Platforms, and Big Cauldrons.

row.Name: Wooden Stairs
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Old unmovable ladder, recipe now produce movable version

row.Name: Wire
row.Description: A metal product that can be used to manufacture Plate Armor, Chainmail Armor, and Scale Armor at a Workbench.

row.Name: Chainmail
row.Description: A metal product that can be used for manufacturing Chainmail Armor at a Workbench.

row.Name: Small metal plate
row.Description: A metal product that can be used to manufacture Plate Armor, Chainmail Armor, Scale Armor at a Workbench. Also used in some parts of Leather Armor and Padded Armor.

row.Name: Metal plate
row.Description: A metal product that can be used to manufacture Plate Armor at a Workbench.

row.Name: Scale strip
row.Description: A metal product that can be used to manufacture Scale Armor at a Workbench.

row.Name: Leather strips
row.Description: A product of Thick Leather that can be used for manufacturing Leather Armor at a Tailor's Bench.

row.Name: Boar Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Boar. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Bull Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Aurochs Bull. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Wolf Head
row.Description: A salvageable part of a slain Wolf. The head can be made into a trophy.

row.Name: Balanced Staff
row.Description: Looks like a regular staff but weighs a little less

row.Name: Sinner's Head
row.Description: Obtained by killing criminals. Used to build a Burning Head.

row.Name: Siege Engineer's Workshops
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Parent of wooden and standard Engineer's Workshop

row.Name: Primitive Boots
row.Description: Even in these shoes you're more comfortable walking

row.Name: Wristbands
row.Description: Doesn't grant much protection, but makes you look somewhat like a warrior

row.Name: Battle Totem
row.Description: Guild leader can place this totem on the territory of an enemy guild to initiate a battle.

row.Name: Starting Island Decorations
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Starting Island decorations group

row.Name: Battle Totem
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Battle totem with container

row.Name: Simple Cloth
row.Description: Simple cloth made from a bundle of Plant Fiber. Used to make Bandages, Primitive Boots, and Wristbands.

row.Name: Building Kit
row.Description: Used in high level buildings such as Keeps, Large Houses, and Workshops.

row.Name: Castle Wall Corner (no merlon, no buttress)
Baromsag tied with a ribbon
row.Description: A gift from a strange boy from Illa-Newydd with a ribbon around it... a piece of dried-up trash that stinks like fresh manure. What is this doing in your bag?

row.Name: Worn-out Pages
row.Description: ...et spiritus Dei ferebatur super aquas ...dixitque Deus fiat lux et facta est lux... A thin piece of finely-made parchment with unfamiliar symbols on it. The characters are oddly straight and neat, like warriors in formation. You peer at the page, and it seems as though its meaning is about to become clear to you, but... no.

row.Name: Self-made Crucifix
row.Description: A strange symbol the likes of which you have never seen - two carefully-worked sticks bound together, one crossed over the other.

row.Name: Bitten Apple
row.Description: A generous gift from the Accur. And lo, this wondrous fruit did ripen 'pon the branch of yonder tree! Tough and ruddy, just like... a maiden's ass!

row.Name: Rotten Cabbage
row.Description: Another gift from the Accur. What a generous old geezer!

row.Name: Fireleaf
row.Description: This pipe herb is a gift from the gods themselves! The peasant is always keen to envelop himself in fragrant clouds of tobacco once his labor is done, as is the warrior after a battle. As is the worker after violence and maiming, or the king after the same... glory to the gods for this wondrous gift!

row.Name: Khtynka
row.Description: This foul trash tastes as bad as it smells. The Khoors mistakenly consider it to be a drink. However, it can hit you even harder than a log to the head... or an edict on new taxes. It brings no joy, but it does help you forget your troubles and purge your mind of thought. That's why the Khoors call it "khtynkhr" - "that which makes one's head wooden."

row.Name: Siege Totem
row.Description: Guild leader can place this totem on the territory of an enemy guild to declare a siege.

row.Name: Quests objects
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Custom indoor objects for quests

row.Name: Premium_Decorations
row.Description: DO NOT TRANSLATE! Unusable furniture and decorations

row.Name: Lesser Battle Totem
